title: Bassist Ron Carter Talks About His Work With A Tribe Called Quest

http_headers.User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/75.0.3740.2 Safari/537.36

fulltitle: Bassist Ron Carter Talks About His Work With A Tribe Called Quest
description:
Legendary bassist Ron Carter (Miles Davis, Herbie Hancock) appears on over 2000 recordings. In this episode Mr. Carter talks with fellow Epifani artist KJ (The Oddysy) about working with Q-Tip and A Tribe Called Quest. 

Ron Carter agreed to play on Low End Theory, but he had one or two conditions. 

This is last of four videos featuring Mr. Carter, shot at his home in New York City during the summer of 2019. At the end KJ ask his bass hero to play a couple of notes. Mr. Carter gives him that and a lot more. This is why he's the most recorded bassist in history. This is why he's the master. 

Interview by KJ (kevin jacoby) of The Oddysy (www.TheOddysy.com)
A/V by Shaper Shifter Labs
Edited by Ruddy Alcantara
